Enum ProxStorGraph

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ProxStorGraph>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<ProxStorGraph>

    public enum ProxStorGraph
extends Enum<ProxStorGraph>
    hold ProxStor instance-wide reference to Graph and provide internal interface to actual back-end graph relational database intercepts: - vertex creation, update, retrieval - edge creation, update, retrieval - graph traversal provides: - transactional related method independent of whether graph instance of TransactionalGraph manages: - indexes
    Author:
    Jim Giannoules

      • start

        public void start(Map<String,String> conf)
           throws ProxStorGraphDatabaseAlreadyRunning
        This is the preferred method to create a new Graph connection instance. Uses a GraphFactory to allow connection to any one of a multitude of back-end graph relational databases.
        Parameters:
        conf - Configuration Map to be passed to GraphFactory
        Throws:
        ProxStorGraphDatabaseAlreadyRunning - If a connection to a database already exists.

        public void shutdown()

        inVertex - Vertex with the in relationship to the Edge
